    {
      "number": 5,
      "id": "PR_kwDOPVzIEM7weFM1",
      "title": "clarify that H1/H2 are used without a new layer of TLS",
      "url": "https://github.com/kazuho/draft-kazuho-ptth-ptth/pull/5",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "kazuho",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Be clear that when H1 or H2 is negotiated, they are used without TLS; the setup channel provides confidentiality and integrity.\r\n\r\nAlso, provide an example of metadata; in this case the intent to shut down the connection (in H1, it's `connection: close`, in H2, it's GOAWAY).",
